name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.datanode.ec.reconstruct.write.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Specifies the maximum amount of bandwidth that the EC reconstruction can utilize for writing.
      When the bandwidth value is zero, there is no limit.

name: file.bytes-per-checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  file.stream-buffer-size

name: dfs.webhdfs.ugi.expire.after.access
description:
How long in milliseconds after the last access
      the cached UGI will expire. With 0, never expire.

name: dfs.webhdfs.netty.high.watermark
description: High watermark configuration to Netty for Datanode WebHdfs.

name: mapreduce.shuffle.port
description:
Default port that the ShuffleHandler will run on. ShuffleHandler
   is a service run at the NodeManager to facilitate transfers of intermediate
   Map outputs to requesting Reducers.

name: io.seqfile.compress.blocksize
description:
The minimum block size for compression in block compressed
          SequenceFiles.

name: dfs.client.block.reader.remote.buffer.size
description:
The output stream buffer size of a DFSClient remote read. The buffer default value is 512B. The buffer includes
      only some request parameters that are: block, blockToken, clientName, startOffset, len, verifyChecksum,
      cachingStrategy.
